16/01/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Eneko Landaburu, director general of enlargement of the European Commission, will arrive in Sofia on Thursday (16 January) to discuss implementation of the new roadmap for EU membership provided at last month's Copenhagen summit. Bulgaria's progress towards EU accession will be assessed and Landaburu will conduct on the spot reviews of projects implemented with EU financial support.
On Wednesday, Prime Minister Simeon Saxe-Coburg said he plans no cabinet changes in the near term, contrary to earlier press reports. He did however suggest there might be changes in the parliamentary group of his ruling party, National Movement Simeon II. (Pari - 16/01/03; BTA, bTV - 15/01/03)
